{
  "text": "For our study, we use \"Algorithmically-Driven Writing Tools\" (ADWTs) as an umbrella term that covers four categories of digital writing tools we included in our research: ChatGPT and the three other categories of digital writing tools classified by Roe et al. (2023), namely, (1) DWAs or digital writing assistants (i.e., Grammarly), (2) MTs or Machine Translators (i.e., Google Translate), and (3) APTs or Automated Paraphrasing Tools (i.e., Quillbot).",
  "mask": "Roe et al. (2023)",
